The **Foot Mount** is a core move in getting your weight lifted from the ground and onto the pole, much like the Basic Foot Hold. It is widely used to modify moves for an extra point of contact, or as a unique way to climb the pole.

[![](https://polepedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/xpole-ad-horizontal-800-%C3%97-328-px.png "xpole ad polepedia")](https://xpoleus.com/shop-all/poles/xpert-pro/xpert-pro-px/affiliate/illunadin/?campaign=move)

**How to Get into the Foot Mount**

**Move Steps**

For a **right-sided** hold, your right foot would be positioned on top.

For a **left-sided** hold, your left foot would be positioned on bottom.

1. Position your foot sideways.
2. Press the arch of your foot firmly into the pole.
3. To move in this hold, simply rotate your foot, maintaining firm pressure in the arch of your foot.

